0 g unsalted butter, chilled and cut into pieces (2 cm)","125 g water","75 g plain flour","1 pinch salt","2 eggs, plus extra 1 egg lightly beaten, for brushing","nigella seeds, for sprinkling"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["100 g smoked salmon, cut into pieces (3 cm)","fresh dill, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r277386","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-18FyK6nf4kY\/XZMwBN5l-4I\/AAAAAAAAaYs\/sjB2x5GVL40TZtvIjkKEE6NMQMrGu4xbACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ufYFZBVq2NU3so90.png","title":"Smoked salmon and preserved lemon choux buns","publishedAt":"2018-05-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.1 g","fat":"8.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"5.1 g","calories":"530.7 kJ \/ 126.4 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, piping bag with plain nozzle (1 cm), toothpick or wooden skewer, pastry brush, wire rack, piping bag with star nozzle (1 cm), refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Choux buns can be made up to 2 days in advance and stored in an airtight sealable container. Fill just before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 20m","12 portions"]}